               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>دیوان عرفی</p>
                     <p>Another MS. of the Diwán of 'Urfi, defective at beginning and end, given to
                        <lb/> me by Dr Rizá Tevfiq (Ridá Tawfiq) in August, 1909. Though imperfect,
                        this <lb/> MS. contains a much larger selection of Urfi's poems than the
                        preceding one. It <lb/> begins in the middle of a qaşida with the verse:</p>
                     <p>هيات متصور نشد آرامش و رم را <lb/> تا رایت عفو و غضبش سایه نیفکند</p>
                     <p>In its present state the MS. (which appears to suffer from numerous
                        dislocations <lb/> and lacunae) comprises 154 ff. of 16'8 x 9'5 c. and 15
                        ll., and is written in a small, <lb/> neat Persian ta'liq between gold
                        lines. A colophon at the end of the ghazals on <lb/> f. 143 is ۱۰۷, which
                        may be meant for 1007/1598-9, or 1070/1659-60.</p>
                  </summary>
